Stagonopleura  is an Australian genus  of the family Estrildidae. It is sometimes absorbed into Emblema.
The genus was established by Ludwig Reichenbach in 1850. The three described species are classified as two subgenera.
They are very similar in appearance, with short red bills, brown upperparts, red rumps and uppertail coverts, and barred or spotted underparts. The informal name of firetails refers to the rich crimson colour at the rump, a prominent characteristic of the genus.The description and arrangement of its infrageneric taxa is: